	<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 xl:py-32 bg-cloud">
		<div class="content-wrapper">
			<h3 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance 2xl:text-7xl">Growing Support for Rewilding</h3>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">Recognising the urgent need for action, there is growing political and societal support for nature restoration in Scotland. The Scottish Government has declared a climate and nature emergency and set ambitious targets for tackling biodiversity loss.</p>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">Key policy developments include:</p>
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-8">
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Scottish Biodiversity Strategy</h4>
					<p>Aims to halt biodiversity loss by 2030 and achieve significant restoration by 2045, explicitly recognising the role of nature restoration and rewilding approaches.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Climate Change Plan</h4>
					<p>Sets targets for reducing emissions, with nature-based solutions like peatland restoration and woodland creation playing a crucial role.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Land Reform</h4>
					<p>Ongoing discussions about land ownership and use aim to empower communities and encourage more sustainable land management.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Funding Mechanisms</h4>
					<p>Various government grants, such as the Nature Restoration Fund and Agri-Environment Climate Scheme (AECS), provide financial support for projects that align with rewilding principles (See our Funding and Support section for details).</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">While challenges remain in translating policy into widespread action on the ground, the direction of travel is positive. Organisations like NatureScot (Scotland's nature agency), Forestry and Land Scotland, and numerous environmental charities are actively involved in supporting and delivering nature restoration projects.</p>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">This supportive context makes Scotland a prime location for pioneering rewilding initiatives.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
